'''Matsusaka Shrine''' (まつさかじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Matsusaka|Q460829|qid=Q460829|1=Matsusaka}}, {{ill|lt=Mie Prefecture|Q128196|qid=Q128196|1=Mie Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}}, and its former modern rank was {{ill|lt=Gosha|Q134917316|qid=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
Its principal deities are {{ill|lt=Emperor Ojin|Q317997|qid=Q317997|lt=Homutawake-no-Mikoto|1=Emperor Ōjin}} ({{ill|lt=Hachiman deity|Q261637|qid=Q261637|1=Hachiman}}) and {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Kami|1=Ukanomitama}} ({{ill|lt=Inari deity|Q719665|qid=Q719665|1=Inari Ōkami}}). Through shrine mergers in the Meiji period, the following deities are also enshrined.

